<component type="desktop-application">
  <id>org.codeberg.trougnouf.cfait</id>
  <name>Cfait</name>
  <summary>Powerful, fast and elegant CalDAV task manager</summary>
  <metadata_license>CC0-1.0</metadata_license>
  <project_license>GPL-3.0-only</project_license>
  <developer_name>Benoit Brummer (Trougnouf)</developer_name>

  <description>
    <p>
      Cfait is designed for speed and stability using Rust. It puts you in control of your data with a local-first approach that syncs seamlessly across your devices via CalDAV.
    </p>
    <p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong
                >Syncs Everywhere:</strong> Compatible with Nextcloud, iCloud, Radicale, and other standard CalDAV servers.</li>
      <li><strong
                >Offline First:</strong> Optimistic UI updates mean you never wait for a server response.</li>
      <li><strong
                >Smart Input:</strong> Typing "Buy cat food !1 @tomorrow" automatically sets priority and due date.</li>
      <li><strong
                >Productivity:</strong> GTD Workflow, Sub-tasks, Dependencies, and Tags.</li>
    </ul>
  </description>

